00:25:37.330 --> 00:25:44.900
So depending on which zones
or districts in the country,

00:25:44.900 --> 00:25:48.500
the populations distribution
there, in some populations

00:25:48.500 --> 00:25:53.470
in some districts, let's say, the
population might be more homogenous

00:25:53.470 --> 00:25:56.120
in terms of the religious makeup.

00:25:56.120 --> 00:26:01.330
And in that -- in those districts,
for instance, in terms of quota,

00:26:01.330 --> 00:26:04.000
there might be maybe four seats

00:26:04.000 --> 00:26:09.670
for the same religious group
allocated for the parliament.

00:26:09.670 --> 00:26:14.170 position:56%
So that the people in that district,
the electors will be voting

00:26:14.170 --> 00:26:18.730
for when they get a list, an
electoral list to vote for.

00:26:18.730 --> 00:26:21.390
They actually see the names
of the candidates and next

00:26:21.390 --> 00:26:23.910
to them are the religious
affiliation

00:26:23.910 --> 00:26:27.040
and then they have several

00:26:27.040 --> 00:26:31.720 position:56%
by specific religious
denomination depending on the makeup

00:26:31.720 --> 00:26:33.830
of the population within
that district.

00:26:33.830 --> 00:26:40.990 position:56%
So that's kind of how it works so it
gives you a little bit of a sense.

