00:27:59.320 --> 00:28:01.430
into a position, into
the electorate, okay,

00:28:01.430 --> 00:28:06.800
can very well be used for a woman.

00:28:06.800 --> 00:28:10.510
In other words, why is the
issue of money being brought

00:28:10.510 --> 00:28:16.720
in when [inaudible] very
wealthy woman [inaudible].

00:28:16.720 --> 00:28:20.740
So why is the money issue an issue?

00:28:20.740 --> 00:28:22.040 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Rouane Itani: Okay, the stakes --

00:28:22.040 --> 00:28:28.280
it's really one of the core
questions which comes at the end

00:28:28.280 --> 00:28:30.470
of the film as a main question.

00:28:30.470 --> 00:28:34.470
So it's a very important
piece of the puzzle.

00:28:34.470 --> 00:28:38.370
And there are various
ways to address this.

00:28:38.370 --> 00:28:40.890
If we cannot go through
the [inaudible] --

00:28:40.890 --> 00:28:43.900
the kind of the chronology of
the history from what you've seen

00:28:43.900 --> 00:28:46.850
in the film, the 10 women who
have ever entered parliament,

00:28:46.850 --> 00:28:50.300
nine of that -- well, we all, many
of them, nine of them actually,

00:28:50.300 --> 00:28:54.050
have come in because of the
man in their family who was

00:28:54.050 --> 00:28:58.400
in the parliament or very close to
power, political power before them

00:28:58.400 --> 00:29:03.510
and they've just kind of filled
in the seat of their father,

00:29:03.510 --> 00:29:05.920
brother, et cetera, husband.

00:29:05.920 --> 00:29:10.920
So there's that one layer that
the women in the first place,

00:29:10.920 --> 00:29:14.460
they're not running
independently and getting in.

00:29:14.460 --> 00:29:16.300
That's also a problem for men too.

00:29:16.300 --> 00:29:18.910
So it's both, it's
everybody that there is kind

00:29:18.910 --> 00:29:21.310
of the Lebanese phenomenon.

00:29:21.310 --> 00:29:27.610
There is that aspect of clanship
or wealthy families who have been

00:29:27.610 --> 00:29:32.600
in power in the past who keep kind
of coming back again and again

00:29:32.600 --> 00:29:35.400 position:56%
and recycling the same family names.

00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:37.620
So the women's representation
is falling under some

00:29:37.620 --> 00:29:40.750
of those situations also.

00:29:40.750 --> 00:29:42.550
And one of the issues
here is looking

00:29:42.550 --> 00:29:44.490
into why aren't there independent
women in the first place?

00:29:44.490 --> 00:29:46.870
And then we can talk about -- yes,
why aren't there independent women

00:29:46.870 --> 00:29:48.640
who are not made part of that whole
general political party blocs,

00:29:48.640 --> 00:29:50.380 position:56%
the major blocs that have the powers
in the country and those that are

00:29:50.380 --> 00:29:51.680
within the system, yet, why
aren't they even running?

00:29:51.680 --> 00:29:52.980
Because there's not
enough women running also.

00:29:52.980 --> 00:29:54.280
So it's multilayered,
it's not just the capital.

00:29:54.280 --> 00:29:56.140
A few years ago, actually, when I
first filmed in 2005, the media,

00:29:56.140 --> 00:29:58.140 position:56%
the access to media to cover a
woman's candidate wasn't equivalent.

00:29:58.140 --> 00:30:02.190
They were giving access to men and
they were lumping all the women

00:30:02.190 --> 00:30:04.710
in kind of like a side bar.

00:30:04.710 --> 00:30:06.940 position:56%
Then there was a change in that law.

00:30:06.940 --> 00:30:11.890
So now the last I know is that
there is equality of media access

00:30:11.890 --> 00:30:17.240
so both men and women candidates
have equal access to show 50%

00:30:17.240 --> 00:30:22.590
of like so that's when men and
women can have access to the media

00:30:22.590 --> 00:30:25.580
to cover their campaigns
when they're running.

00:30:25.580 --> 00:30:27.010
So that's an improvement.

00:30:27.010 --> 00:30:30.680
So there was one [inaudible],
the question of budget was coming

00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:37.160
into that it require a lot of
money to buy media spots or access

00:30:37.160 --> 00:30:40.960
to the media to publicize oneself
and to run a campaign in general.

00:30:40.960 --> 00:30:48.120
Women have been found to be
campaign managers for men.

00:30:48.120 --> 00:30:53.190 position:56%
But it's kind of like the whole
structure hasn't been created enough

00:30:53.190 --> 00:30:57.260
at least yet for women
candidates to figure out how

00:30:57.260 --> 00:31:03.670
to channel all not just the money
but the support, the mechanism,

00:31:03.670 --> 00:31:07.140
the whole structure of campaigning
and promoting themselves.

00:31:07.140 --> 00:31:09.690
So there's all of that.

00:31:09.690 --> 00:31:14.580
In addition, the question
of access to money

00:31:14.580 --> 00:31:19.100
for women might be a little
complex because there are women

00:31:19.100 --> 00:31:23.240 position:56%
